From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000108 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 11:45:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] misc: keep Fruit Jam HCD handshake scan passive

Pico-PIO-USB's RX path uses IRQ4 as the live NRZI decoder trigger. The HCD
setup-handshake scanner added in the previous patch cleared RX_ALL while
waiting, which can clear DECODER_TRIGGER in the middle of a packet and perturb
the exact handshake/data stream being measured.

The receive window is already cleared before the scanner starts. Make the scan
loop passive: drain RX FIFO bytes, observe IRQ state for quiet/timeout
bookkeeping, and leave RX_START/RX_EOP/DECODER_TRIGGER ownership to the PIO
program until the scanner disables RX at the end.
---
 drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
--- a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
@@ -3162,8 +3162,6 @@ static int fj_usbhost_pio_wait_handshake_scan(struct fruitjam_usbhost *uh,
 		}
 
 		irq = readl(uh->pio + FJ_PIO_IRQ);
-		if (irq & FJ_PIO_IRQ_RX_ALL)
-			writel(FJ_PIO_IRQ_RX_ALL, uh->pio + FJ_PIO_IRQ);
 		if (len != before || (irq & (FJ_PIO_IRQ_RX_EOP |
 					     FJ_PIO_IRQ_RX_START |
 					     FJ_PIO_IRQ_DECODER_TRIGGER))) {
